### 🧪 Ultra-Granular TVOC Thresholds with Colour Coding and Hex Values

| **Level** | **TVOC Range (ppb)** | **Approx. µg/m³** | **Air Quality Description**                                                                 | **Colour Name**     | **Hex Code** |
|-----------|----------------------|-------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------|--------------|
| A1        | 0 – 25               | 0 – ~0.12         | Ultra-pristine air; filtered cleanrooms or outdoor rural settings                          | Emerald Green        | #009E60      |
| A2        | 26 – 50              | ~0.13 – ~0.24     | Exceptionally clean; ideal for sensitive environments                                      | Forest Green         | #228B22      |
| A3        | 51 – 75              | ~0.25 – ~0.37     | Very low VOC presence; no odour or irritation risk                                         | Leaf Green           | #32CD32      |
| B1        | 76 – 100             | ~0.38 – ~0.49     | Excellent indoor air; optimal for all occupants                                            | Lime Green           | #BFFF00      |
| B2        | 101 – 125            | ~0.50 – ~0.61     | Very good; minimal VOCs, no health concerns                                                | Pale Green           | #98FB98      |
| B3        | 126 – 150            | ~0.62 – ~0.73     | Good air quality; suitable for long-term exposure                                          | Light Yellow         | #FFFFE0      |
| C1        | 151 – 175            | ~0.74 – ~0.85     | Acceptable; low-level VOCs may be detectable by sensitive individuals                     | Yellow               | #FFFF00      |
| C2        | 176 – 200            | ~0.86 – ~0.98     | Slightly elevated; odour possible, no health risk                                          | Amber                | #FFBF00      |
| C3        | 201 – 225            | ~0.99 – ~1.10     | Fair; mild discomfort possible in enclosed spaces                                          | Light Orange         | #FFD580      |
| D1        | 226 – 250            | ~1.11 – ~1.22     | Borderline moderate; ventilation may be beneficial                                         | Orange               | #FFA500      |
| D2        | 251 – 275            | ~1.23 – ~1.34     | Moderate; symptoms possible in sensitive groups                                            | Deep Orange          | #FF8C00      |
| D3        | 276 – 300            | ~1.35 – ~1.47     | Upper limit of “Good”; approaching warning zone                                            | Burnt Orange         | #CC5500      |
| E1        | 301 – 400            | ~1.48 – ~1.96     | Warning zone; odours and irritation may occur                                              | Light Red            | #FF6666      |
| E2        | 401 – 500            | ~1.97 – ~2.45     | Elevated VOCs; ventilation recommended                                                     | Red                  | #FF0000      |
| E3        | 501 – 600            | ~2.46 – ~2.94     | Moderate pollution; complaints likely                                                      | Crimson              | #DC143C      |
| F1        | 601 – 750            | ~2.95 – ~3.68     | Poor air quality; symptoms expected                                                        | Dark Red             | #8B0000      |
| F2        | 751 – 1000           | ~3.69 – ~4.90     | Alert level; unsafe for prolonged exposure                                                 | Brick Red            | #B22222      |
| G1        | 1001 – 1500          | ~4.91 – ~7.35     | High VOCs; urgent action required                                                          | Brown                | #A52A2A      |
| G2        | 1501 – 2000          | ~7.36 – ~9.80     | Very poor; acute symptoms likely                                                           | Dark Brown           | #5C4033      |
| G3        | 2001 – 3000          | ~9.81 – ~14.70    | Hazardous; evacuation or ventilation essential                                             | Maroon Black         | #3B0A0A      |
| H1        | > 3000               | > ~14.70          | Severe pollution; toxic exposure risk                                                      | Black                | #000000      |

