### 🍷 Ultra-Granular Ethanol Index Thresholds with Colour Coding and Hex Values

| **Level** | **Ethanol Index Value** | **Description**                                                                 | **Colour Name**     | **Hex Code** |
|-----------|--------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------|--------------|
| A1        | 0.00 – 0.05              | Baseline; no ethanol detected                                                  | Emerald Green        | #009E60      |
| A2        | 0.06 – 0.10              | Trace ethanol; typical of unoccupied spaces                                    | Forest Green         | #228B22      |
| B1        | 0.11 – 0.15              | Very low ethanol; may result from human respiration                            | Leaf Green           | #32CD32      |
| B2        | 0.16 – 0.20              | Low ethanol; background from mild product use                                  | Pale Green           | #98FB98      |
| C1        | 0.21 – 0.25              | Light ethanol presence; no health concern                                      | Light Yellow         | #FFFFE0      |
| C2        | 0.26 – 0.30              | Slightly elevated; odour may be perceptible                                    | Yellow               | #FFFF00      |
| D1        | 0.31 – 0.35              | Moderate ethanol; ventilation may be beneficial                                | Amber                | #FFBF00      |
| D2        | 0.36 – 0.40              | Noticeable ethanol; may cause mild irritation                                  | Orange               | #FFA500      |
| E1        | 0.41 – 0.45              | Elevated ethanol; approaching alert threshold                                  | Light Red            | #FF6666      |
| E2        | 0.46 – 0.50              | High ethanol; alert may trigger depending on context                           | Red                  | #FF0000      |
| F1        | 0.51 – 0.60              | Alert zone; strong ethanol presence from sprays or solvents                    | Crimson              | #DC143C      |
| F2        | 0.61 – 0.70              | High ethanol; discomfort likely in enclosed spaces                             | Dark Red             | #8B0000      |
| G1        | 0.71 – 0.80              | Very high ethanol; ventilation strongly advised                                | Brown                | #A52A2A      |
| G2        | 0.81 – 0.90              | Severe ethanol spike; possible spill or misuse                                 | Dark Brown           | #5C4033      |
| H1        | 0.91 – 1.00              | Dangerous ethanol level; flammability or toxicity risk                         | Maroon Black         | #3B0A0A      |
| H2        | > 1.00                   | Excessive ethanol; immediate action required                                   | Black                | #000000      |

